                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d550">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">713.1311/296: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-15T18:00:00-06:00"
                            >March 15, 1934—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:56 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>27. My 26, March 15, noon. The Conference selected Doctor Reina Andrade of the
                    Guatemalan delegation for permanent chairman and adjourned until next Monday.
                    Committees were not named.</p>
                <p>The delegations are being accorded a warm and enthusiastic welcome by the
                    Guatemalan Government and people and a friendly spirit prevails.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
